<p>However, this approach has limitations as it cannot set certain attributes like <strong><em>HttpOnly</em></strong> which are crucial for security.</p>
<p>You can refer to <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/cookie">MDN's Extensive documentation</a> on cookies for more details and examples.</p>
<h2>Best Practices for Using Cookies</h2>
<p>When working with cookies, consider these best practices:</p>
<ol>
<li>Use the HttpOnly flag for session cookies to prevent XSS attacks.</li>
<li>Use the Secure flag to ensure cookies are only transmitted over HTTPS.</li>
<li>Implement proper CSRF protection for cookies that are used for session management.</li>
<li>Use the SameSite attribute to prevent CSRF and information leakage.</li>
<li>Don't store sensitive information in cookies unless it's absolutely necessary.</li>
<li>Be mindful of cookie size limitations (generally 4KB per cookie).</li>
<li>Consider the implications of EU cookie laws and obtain user consent when necessary.</li>
